    <div class="project-description">
        <p>A personal website built for experimenting with new ideas.</p>
        <p>
            I chose to use .NET Blazor as development framework because I was interested in using C# for my code-behind instead of a JavaScript variant. I wanted a strongly-typed system with the familiarity of C#.
            I used Github Actions to automatically deploy my static website to AWS S3 every time I created an update to the master branch to simplify my deployment process.
            I used Cloudflare for their free-tier caching and DNS services.
        </p>
